a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"88";s:3:"url";s:3:"n/A";s:9:"publisher";s:12:"Miami Herald";s:6:"author";s:14:"Rene Rodriguez";s:6:"review";s:349:"Madrid, 1987 operates on a dizzying number of levels - as a romantic comedy, a sex farce, a study of culture clash, ageism and idealism - and the highest compliment you can give this ridiculously talky movie (which plays better if you speak Spanish) is that you're a little sad to see the characters go on their way once they part, probably forever.";}i:1;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"70";s:3:"url";s:90:"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/madrid-1987-sundance-review-283889/";s:9:"publisher";s:22:"The Hollywood Reporter";s:6:"author";s:11:"John DeFore";s:6:"review";s:240:"An engrossing two-hander combining the smart-talk microcosm of "My Dinner With Andre" and the sexual dynamics of a Philip Roth novel, David Trueba's Madrid, 1987 is more universal than its title suggests and holds a strong art house appeal.";}i:2;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"70";s:3:"url";s:61:"https://variety.com/2011/film/reviews/madrid-1987-1117946745/";s:9:"publisher";s:7:"Variety";s:6:"author";s:16:"Jonathan Holland";s:6:"review";s:239:"A perceptive, ultra-wordy stab at catching the zeitgeist at a time of change in Spain, David Trueba's two-hander nonetheless feels like a working-out of social and personal themes that hasn't quite achieved the full leap from page to film.";}i:3;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"70";s:3:"url";s:3:"n/A";s:9:"publisher";s:13:"Village Voice";s:6:"author";s:3:"n/A";s:6:"review";s:140:"Miguel uses her beauty and placid demeanor as a screen against which to project his memories of past adventures and the ghost of his libido.";}i:4;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"60";s:3:"url";s:27:"https://help.azcentral.com/";s:9:"publisher";s:16:"Arizona Republic";s:6:"author";s:3:"n/A";s:6:"review";s:81:"Deserves commendation for its fearless bravado, if for little else. [25 Oct 2012]";}i:5;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"50";s:3:"url";s:112:"https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-xpm-2012-oct-25-la-et-mn-madrid-1987-capsule-20121026-story.html";s:9:"publisher";s:17:"Los Angeles Times";s:6:"author";s:3:"n/A";s:6:"review";s:121:"The actors give their characters a resonance beyond the symbolic, but the action doesn't quite transcend the stagy setup.";}i:6;a:5:{s:6:"rating";s:2:"40";s:3:"url";s:94:"https://www.nytimes.com/2012/10/12/movies/madrid-1987-directed-by-david-trueba.html?ref=movies";s:9:"publisher";s:18:"The New York Times";s:6:"author";s:3:"n/A";s:6:"review";s:45:"Sweet, sometimes dull and certainly overlong.";}}